Wash and dry produce.

Halve @lemon{1/2}. Tear or slice @prosciutto{2%ounce} into bite-size pieces.

Place @whole wheat pitas{2%unit} on a #microwave-safe plate{}. Reserve 1 TBSP 
@Italian cheese blend{1%tbsp} for serving; top pitas with remaining 
@Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Microwave until cheese just melts and pitas are 
soft, ~{40-50%seconds}. (You may need to microwave in batches.)

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @fig jam{1}, juice from half the lemon 
(whole lemon for 4 servings), a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, a pinch of 
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. 
Add @arugula{2%ounce}, @pecans{1/2%ounce}, and half the prosciutto; toss 
until thoroughly coated.

Cut cheesy pitas into quarters and sprinkle with remaining prosciutto. Top with 
salad and reserved Italian cheese blend.

Divide pita pizzas between #plates{} and serve.

> It's a sweet two-for-one lunch idea that's hard to pass up!